            <button class="slider-arrow right" id="nextImage">›</button>
          </div>

          <div class="product-thumbs">
            <img
              class="thumb-image active-thumb"
              src="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-s200.jpg"
              alt="ST-S200 Thumbnail"
              data-full="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-s200.jpg"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="product-summary">
          <h1>ST-S200 Mini Ionizer Fan</h1>
          <p class="product-short-desc">
            ST-S200 mini ionizer fan — magnetic levitation airflow, AC 100–240V input,
            ±15V ion balance, 150~450mm effective range, low noise, CE certified
            for electronics workstations and precision assembly.
          </p>

          <div class="product-actions">
            <button class="quote-btn" type="button">Get a Quote</button>
            <a href="https://wa.me/61436605126" target="_blank" class="whatsapp-btn">WhatsApp</a>
          </div>

          <div class="product-highlights">
            <div class="highlight-item">
              <h4>Magnetic Levitation Airflow</h4>
              <p>All-new magnetic levitation design delivers smooth, quiet airflow for workstation use.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="highlight-item">
              <h4>150~450mm Range</h4>
              <p>Effective emission distance covers typical workstation and benchtop applications.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="highlight-item">
              <h4>Universal AC Input</h4>
              <p>AC 100–240V, 50/60Hz input works worldwide without a transformer.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Product Description</h2>
        <p>
          The ST-S200 Mini Ionizer Fan features an all-new magnetic levitation airflow design for
          smooth, quiet operation. High-efficiency DC high voltage generates positive and negative
          air ions that neutralize static charges on work surfaces within a 150~450mm effective range.
        </p>
        <p>
          Its compact size makes it easy to install at workstations and benchtop applications. The
          self-diagnostic protection circuit with overcurrent protection ensures safe operation, while
          the low noise design and long service life make it ideal for cleanroom, precision assembly,
          semiconductor handling, and electronics inspection environments. CE certified and universally
          compatible with AC 100–240V input.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Product Features</h2>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li>All-new design with magnetic levitation airflow — smooth and quiet operation</li>
          <li>High-efficiency DC high voltage generating positive and negative air ions</li>
          <li>Compact size — easy to install in workstations and benchtop applications</li>
          <li>High-quality DC high voltage module for superior static elimination performance</li>
          <li>Self-diagnostic protection circuit with overcurrent protection</li>
          <li>CE certified — meets safety standards</li>
          <li>Low noise, long service life</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Technical Advantages</h2>
        <div class="advantage-grid">
          <div class="advantage-card blue">
            <h3>Magnetic Levitation Fan</h3>
            <p>Smooth, quiet airflow from magnetic levitation design — ideal for precision workstation environments.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-card yellow">
            <h3>Wide Input Voltage</h3>
            <p>AC 100–240V universal input works in any country without additional power conversion.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-card green">
            <h3>CE Certified</h3>
            <p>Meets international safety standards for use in professional manufacturing and cleanroom environments.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Technical Specifications</h2>
        <div class="spec-table-wrap">
          <table class="spec-table">
            <tr><td>Model</td><td>ST-S200</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Power Input</td><td>AC 100–240V, 50/60Hz</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Ion Output</td><td>Positive and negative air ions</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Ion Balance</td><td>±15V or better</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Emission Distance</td><td>150~450mm effective range</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Airflow</td><td>Adjustable</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Noise Level</td><td>Low noise design</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Working Temperature</td><td>0~40°C</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Working Humidity</td><td>20~85% RH</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Certification</td><td>CE certified</td></tr>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Industry Applications</h2>
        <div class="application-tags">
          <span>Electronics Workstations</span>
          <span>PCB Inspection</span>
          <span>Semiconductor Handling</span>
          <span>Cleanroom</span>
          <span>Precision Assembly</span>
          <span>Testing Benches</span>
        </div>
      </section>


      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Application Scenarios</h2>
        <div class="scenario-list">
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Robotic Arm and Gantry-Mounted Static Control</h3>
            <p>Automated assembly systems require static control that moves with the process. The ST-S200's compact size and light weight make it suitable for mounting directly on robotic arms, pick-and-place heads, or gantry systems, delivering targeted ionization exactly where ESD-sensitive components are handled without adding significant weight or bulk to the moving assembly.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Confined Space and Small Workstation Applications</h3>
            <p>When workspace is limited and a full-sized ionizing blower cannot fit, the ST-S200 delivers effective static elimination within its 150–450 mm effective range from a much smaller footprint. It is ideal for optical lens inspection stages, precision measurement stations, and compact assembly fixtures where every centimeter of bench space matters.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Cleanroom and Vibration-Sensitive Environments</h3>
            <p>The magnetic levitation fan design eliminates mechanical bearing vibration, making the ST-S200 suitable for cleanroom environments and vibration-sensitive processes where conventional fan motors would introduce unwanted mechanical noise. The near-silent operation also makes it comfortable for environments where operators work in close proximity to the ionizer for long periods.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>How to Choose the Right Ionizer</h2>
        <p>Choose the ST-S200 when space is limited, mounting flexibility is required, or vibration-free operation is critical. For larger workbench coverage, the <a href="/products/static-eliminator/st-101a">ST101A</a> (40 cm × 60 cm) or <a href="/products/static-eliminator/st-104a">ST104A</a> (60 cm × 120 cm) provide greater air volume and coverage area. For inline conveyor applications, an <a href="/products/static-eliminator/st-e-series">ion bar</a> is generally more appropriate. If you need to eliminate static on a moving automated system, the ST-S200 is typically the best fit.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block faq-block">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What is magnetic levitation airflow and why does it matter?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The ST-S200 uses a magnetic levitation (maglev) fan motor that eliminates mechanical bearings. This results in near-silent operation, negligible vibration, and significantly longer fan lifespan compared to conventional brushed or bushing fan motors — important for precision and cleanroom environments where vibration and noise are concerns.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">How does the ST-S200 compare to the ST101A ionizing blower?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The ST-S200 is a compact mini ionizer fan optimized for tight spaces and robotic mounting, with a 150–450 mm working range. The ST101A is a larger desktop blower with higher air volume covering 40 cm × 60 cm at the workstation level. Choose the ST-S200 for space-constrained or moving-mounted applications; choose the ST101A for standard workbench static control.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Can the ST-S200 be mounted on a robotic arm?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">Yes. The ST-S200's compact dimensions and light weight make it suitable for direct mounting on robotic arms, gantries, and automated positioning systems, delivering ionization that follows the process rather than requiring the process to pass through a fixed ion field.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What is the effective static elimination range of the ST-S200?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The ST-S200 has an effective ionization range of 150–450 mm, allowing flexible positioning at workstations without requiring extremely close proximity to the target surface.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Does the ST-S200 need a special power supply?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">No. The ST-S200 operates on standard AC 100–240V, 50/60Hz mains power, making it compatible worldwide without additional voltage conversion.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Is the ST-S200 suitable for cleanroom use?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">Yes. The low-vibration, low-noise magnetic levitation design and compact form make the ST-S200 well suited for cleanroom environments, optical inspection stations, and sensitive semiconductor assembly processes where conventional fan-based ionizers may introduce unacceptable vibration or particle generation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <div class="related-slider-wrap" data-current="st-s200">
          <div class="related-slider-header">
            <h2>Related Products</h2>
            <div class="related-slider-nav">
              <button class="related-slider-btn related-slider-prev" type="button">‹</button>
              <button class="related-slider-btn related-slider-next" type="button">›</button>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="related-slider-track">
            <a href="/products/static-eliminator/st-g-series" class="related-slide-card" data-key="st-g-series">
